com.esri.mo2.data.feat
Interface Cursor

All Known Implementing Classes:
BaseCursor, DbaseCursor, ElementCursor, TransformationCursor
public interface Cursor

A Cursor is a collection of Data objects that can be accessed sequentially. A Cursor is usually obtained by executing a Searchable Dataset's search method.

See Also:
Searchable, Dataset, Data

dispose

public void dispose()
This method should be invoked after you have finished using the Cursor, to clear resources. This is considered necessary in the Java environment, as Cursors are created relatively frequently, and you may need to save memory prior to the next GC operation.
